item.description:
In the previous article we saw how to use request parameters and request body of a request. In this article we will see how to use the request headers.
The request headers can be accessed using the @RequestHeader attribute.
@RequestMapping(&#34;/greeting&#34;) public ResponseEntity&lt;String&gt; greeting(@RequestHeader(&#34;Accept-Language&#34;) String language, @RequestHeader(&#34;Content-Type&#34;) String contentType) { // do something with the headers return new ResponseEntity&lt;String&gt;(String.format(&#34;Language: %s, Content Type: %s&#34;, language, contentType), HttpStatus.OK); } Note that the name of the header field is case insensitive.
